<!-- FAQ -->
<!-- LOCAL KNOWLEDGE (Maple Ridge) -->
<section id="local" style="padding:5rem 2.5rem;background:#f9f8f6">
  <div style="max-width:1180px;margin:0 auto">
    <div style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:.5rem"><span class="section-label">Local Knowledge</span></div>
    <h2 class="section-title" style="text-align:center">Injury &amp; ICBC Claims in Maple Ridge: What to Know</h2>
    <p style="text-align:center;max-width:680px;margin:1rem auto 0;color:var(--muted);font-size:1rem;line-height:1.65">Maple Ridge sees thousands of collisions and injury claims every year. If you have been hurt in or around Maple Ridge, here is the local context that shapes your claim.</p>
    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(240px,1fr));gap:1.5rem;margin-top:2.5rem">
      <div style="background:#fff;border:1px solid #e8e4dc;border-radius:14px;padding:1.6rem"><h3 style="font-family:'Playfair Display',serif;color:var(--navy);font-size:1.12rem;margin-bottom:.6rem">Where Maple Ridge crashes happen</h3><p style="color:var(--muted);font-size:.92rem;line-height:1.65">The Lougheed Highway, the Golden Ears Way and Bridge, Dewdney Trunk Road, and the Haney Bypass carry the area's heaviest traffic.</p></div>
      <div style="background:#fff;border:1px solid #e8e4dc;border-radius:14px;padding:1.6rem"><h3 style="font-family:'Playfair Display',serif;color:var(--navy);font-size:1.12rem;margin-bottom:.6rem">ICBC &amp; your claim</h3><p style="color:var(--muted);font-size:.92rem;line-height:1.65">Most BC auto injuries run through ICBC, whose Enhanced Care system provides medical and wage benefits regardless of fault. We make sure ICBC pays the full benefits you are owed, challenge denials and low offers, and pursue every additional claim the law still allows. Under BC's Limitation Act you generally have <strong>2 years</strong> to act.</p></div>
      <div style="background:#fff;border:1px solid #e8e4dc;border-radius:14px;padding:1.6rem"><h3 style="font-family:'Playfair Display',serif;color:var(--navy);font-size:1.12rem;margin-bottom:.6rem">Getting treated</h3><p style="color:var(--muted);font-size:.92rem;line-height:1.65">Ridge Meadows Hospital handles local emergencies, with major trauma going to Royal Columbian Hospital. Keep every record and receipt.</p></div>
      <div style="background:#fff;border:1px solid #e8e4dc;border-radius:14px;padding:1.6rem"><h3 style="font-family:'Playfair Display',serif;color:var(--navy);font-size:1.12rem;margin-bottom:.6rem">Where your claim is heard</h3><p style="color:var(--muted);font-size:.92rem;line-height:1.65">Larger lawsuits go to the BC Supreme Court at New Westminster, while many ICBC disputes are handled through the Civil Resolution Tribunal (CRT).</p></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="faq">
  <div class="section-wrap">
    <div style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0">
      <span class="section-label">Common Questions</span>
      <h2 class="section-title" data-stc="faq_city">Personal Injury Questions in Maple Ridge</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-grid">
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q" data-faq="faq_cost" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
          How much does a personal injury lawyer cost in Maple Ridge?
          <span class="faq-arrow">&#8964;</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-a">Sidhu Legal works on a contingency fee basis. You pay nothing upfront and we only collect a fee if we win your case. Your initial consultation is always completely free.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q" data-faq="faq_bc_limit" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
          How long do I have to file a claim after an injury in BC?
          <span class="faq-arrow">&#8964;</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-a">In British Columbia, the general limitation period is 2 years from the date of injury. For ICBC claims, there are even shorter notice requirements. Contact us as soon as possible to protect your rights.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q" data-faq="faq_icbc_offer" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
          What if ICBC has already made me an offer?
          <span class="faq-arrow">&#8964;</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-a">Do not accept any ICBC settlement without speaking to a lawyer first. Once you sign a release you cannot reopen your claim. ICBC's first offers are almost always far below what injured claimants are entitled to receive.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q" data-faq="faq_fault" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
          Can I claim if the accident was partly my fault?
          <span class="faq-arrow">&#8964;</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-a">Yes. BC follows a contributory negligence framework. Even if you share some fault, you may still recover compensation proportional to the other party's share of responsibility. Call us to discuss your specific situation.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q" data-faq="faq_bc_serve" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
          Do you serve clients outside of Maple Ridge?
          <span class="faq-arrow">&#8964;</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-a">Yes. We serve clients across the Lower Mainland and Fraser Valley including Pitt Meadows, Mission, Port Coquitlam, Surrey, Langley, and beyond. Most consultations and meetings can be done by phone or video call.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q" data-faq="faq_time" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
          How long does a personal injury case typically take?
          <span class="faq-arrow">&#8964;</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-a">It varies based on the complexity of the case and the severity of your injuries. Straightforward cases can settle in a few months. Complex cases may take one to three years. After reviewing your situation, we will give you a realistic and honest timeline.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

